<TITLE> Two cases filed against militant suspects at Bagmara </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com)Two cases were filed on Friday against the three leaders of 'Islam and Muslim', a newly formed militant group, at Bagmara Police Station of Rajshahi. The defendants are Abdur Rahim alias Shahadat, Sajedur Rahman alias Hanif and Jalal Uddin alias Jalal. Sub-inspector of Bagmara Police Station Firoz Kabir filed the cases under section 19 (Ka) of Arms Act and section 8, 9, 10 of Anti-terrorism Ordinance-2008. Police took the suspected militants to Rajshahi Judicial Magistrate's Court-3 and appealed to remand hem in custody for seven days. The Court sent them to jail and set Sunday for hearing. The Bagmara police chief said they pressed murder charges against top leader Abdur Rahim alias Shahadat. He also faces murder and robbery charges filed with Gomostapur Police Station of Chanpainawabganj. The Special Branch of police brought them to Bagmara from Dhaka in the early in the morning. They were arrested on Thursday along with two suspected JMB militants in a sting. The SB also detained Jalaluddin, the Baghmara thana JMB commander in Rajshahi, with a crude Indian-made gun and five bullets. The Special Branch made the arrests at Jaydebpur in Gazipur and Baghmara in Rajshahi from June 28 to 30. Some Jihad literature was also seized. Montu already stands convicted for 31 years. All of the detainees denied any wrongdoing. The new group was formed by trained militants who were formerly members of Jamaat-ul-Mujahideen Bangladesh, said a statement given to reporters at a press briefing in the capital's Special Branch office. bdne
